Copper in London Declines for a Third Day; New York Futures Drop

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-02-23T01:09:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/copper-drops-for-third-day-on-concern-mideast-unrest-may-derail-recovery.html
Copper declined for a third day in  London  on concern escalating geopolitical tensions may derail
the global economic recovery. The metal also dropped in  New
York .  Three-month delivery copper on the London Metal Exchange
fell as much as 0.6 percent to $9,524 a metric ton, while May-
delivery futures on the Comex in New York shed as much as 0.7
percent to $4.3320 a pound.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  